<TITLE> Villagers kill tiger after death of three in Satkhira </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, June 21 (bdnews24.com)  Local people beat a tiger to death Saturday after the animal strayed into the locality from the Sundarbans and killed three villagers in Satkhira, an official said. "People kept the tiger in captivity overnight before killing the animal in the morning," local Union Parishad chairman Mojibur Rahman told bdnews24.com. Solaiman Hossain, Kadamtala station officer under Satrkhira forest range, said the tiger entered a village in Shyamnagar upazila around 9pm Friday. Tarok Chandra, a villager, was the first to come under attack. He bled to death on the scene. Later, the tiger killed Aghor Mondol and daughter-in-law Korunabala at their home, Solaiman said. bdnews24.c
